### Docker Security

Secure Dockerfile practices:

```dockerfile
# ✅ GOOD - Security best practices
FROM ubuntu:22.04

# Use non-root user when possible
RUN useradd -m -u 1000 scanner && \
    mkdir -p /work && \
    chown scanner:scanner /work

# Don't install unnecessary packages
RUN apt-get update && \
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        ca-certificates \
        curl \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

# Verify checksums for downloaded binaries
RUN curl -fsSL https://example.com/tool.tar.gz -o /tmp/tool.tar.gz && \
    echo "expected_checksum  /tmp/tool.tar.gz" | sha256sum -c - && \
    tar -xzf /tmp/tool.tar.gz -C /usr/local/bin && \
    rm /tmp/tool.tar.gz

# Run as non-root
USER scanner
WORKDIR /work
```

## Security Testing

### Static Analysis

Use security-focused static analysis tools:

```bash
# Semgrep for security patterns
semgrep --config=auto --config=p/security-audit

# Bandit for Python security issues
bandit -r sec_audit/

# Safety for dependency vulnerabilities
safety check
```

### Dynamic Testing

Test security controls:

```python
# ✅ GOOD - Security test example
def test_path_traversal_prevention():
    """Test that path traversal attacks are prevented."""
    malicious_repo = "../../etc/passwd"
    with pytest.raises(ValueError, match="Invalid"):
        clone_repo(malicious_repo, Path("/tmp/test"), "main", False)

def test_command_injection_prevention():
    """Test that command injection is prevented."""
    malicious_branch = "main; rm -rf /"
    # Should not execute rm command
    result = clone_repo("https://example.com/repo.git", 
                       Path("/tmp/test"), 
                       malicious_branch, 
                       False)
    # Verify only git clone was executed
```

## Reporting Security Issues

When security vulnerabilities are found:

1. Document in audit reports with severity (Critical/High/Medium/Low)
2. Include exploit scenario and impact
3. Provide concrete remediation steps
4. Reference CVE/GHSA if applicable
5. Include code snippets showing vulnerable and fixed code
